Chris receives 12 strawberries.

Calculate the total number of strawberries shared.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\item In a sale, a shop reduces all prices by 12\%.

\begin{subparts}
\subpart Dina buys a book which has an original price of \$6.50.

Calculate how much Dina pays for the book.

\AnswerLine[\$][]
\Marks{2}

\subpart Elu pays \$11 for a toy.

Calculate the original price of the toy.

\AnswerLine[\$][]
\Marks{2}

\end{subparts}

\item Feri invests some money.\\
The rate of interest for the first year is 2.5\%.\\
At the end of the second year the overall percentage increase of Feri's investment is 6.6\%.

Find the rate of interest for the second year.

\AnswerLine[][\%]
\Marks{2}

\item A radioactive substance decays at an exponential rate of 2\% per day.\\
The initial mass is 80\,g.

\begin{subparts}
\subpart Find the mass at the end of 5 days.

\AnswerLine[][g]
\Marks{2}

\subpart Find how many \textbf{more} whole days, after day 5, it takes for the mass to reduce to less than 67\,g.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{3}

\end{subparts}

\end{parts}

